Moves Walking ... picked up a pointed stick and, after offering it to
Wakan-Tanka, drew a line in the soft earth, from the west to the east;
after offering the stick again to the heavens, he drew another line
from the north to the south. Finally, the altar was completed by
making two lines of tobacco on top of the two paths drawn on the
ground, and then this tobacco was painted red. This altar now
represented the universe and all that is in it. At its center was
Wakan-Tanka; His presence was really there in the altar, and that is
why it was made in such a careful and sacred way.
